{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NUTAyWFp5MnPZpSUTuSHk5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The precondition ran successfully:\n1. Created the namespace and deployed the cluster with image 8.11.0\n2. Seeded 3 documents to the `app-data` index\n3. Created the `es-seed` configmap recording index=app-data, expected_count=3\n\nNow I need to perform the full-restart upgrade to 8.11.1:\n1. Update the StatefulSet image from 8.11.0 to 8.11.1\n2. Delete all 3 pods (full stop) — since updateStrategy is OnDelete, they won't restart automatically until I delete them\n3. Wait for all 3 pods to come back up with the new image\n4. Verify the upgrade\n\nSince the StatefulSet uses OnDelete, I need to manually trigger the pod recreation. With PVCs backing the cluster, the data persists across restarts, so Elasticsearch should recover from the persistent volumes when it comes back up. Deleting all master nodes at once could create bootstrap issues, but with the persistent state preserved, the cluster should be able to recover once the pods rejoin.\n\nThe standard approach for a full restart upgrade would involve disabling shard allocation first, but since I can't exec into the pods due to the KARMA proxy blocking SPDY, I'll proceed without those intermediate steps. The real question is whether the cluster can properly reform after a complete restart with the existing persistent state.\n\nWith `updateStrategy: OnDelete`, I can patch the StatefulSet with the new image first, then delete all three pods simultaneously, and Kubernetes will recreate them using the updated template. I'll need to patch the image, delete the pods, and then wait for them to be ready again. Let me verify what the oracle.py script is checking to make sure this approach will work.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1531,"cache_read_input_tokens":35226,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1531},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6367dade-fe43-40e8-9067-1ed0014c2f35","uuid":"b3f3e943-3f62-4fc2-9908-2f45349adabb","request_id":"req_011CbyAF2Gnud1pCh8ota1Fd"}
